{% block page_content %}
<h3 id="intro">Intro</h3>
<p>
  {{ link::e(path="https://opengear.com/", description="Opengear") }} is a terminal 
  server that is commonly used to connect to infrastructure 
  devices via an out of band network or console/serial port.
</p>
<p>
  This post covers some of the common commands and operations
  that I usually undertake with opengear devices.
</p>

<h3 id="connecting">Connecting</h3>
<p>
  SSH to an opengear and open the serial menu.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code="ssh &lt;username&gt;:serial@&lt;ip-address&gt;"
) }}

<h3 id="menu">Menu</h3>
<p>
  Return to the serial menu.
</p>
<p>
  On a new line press {{ text::kbd(text="~") }}
 {{ text::kbd(text=".") }}
 then {{ text::kbd(text="enter") }}

</p>
{% endblock page_content %}